import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x="state", data=data, order=data['state'].value_counts().index)
    ax.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Number of Zip Codes')
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate(format(p.get_height(), '.0f'), (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), ha = 'center', va = 'center', xytext = (0, 10), textcoords = 'offset points')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different states?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x="city", data=data, order=data['city'].value_counts().index[:10])
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha="right")
    ax.set_xlabel('City')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')
    ax.axhline(y=data['city'].value_counts().max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Zip Codes')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
